(1, '{\"en\":\"The History of the Security Council of the Republic of Artsakh (Nagorno Karabakh)\",\"hy\":\"\\u0531\\u0580\\u0581\\u0561\\u056d\\u056b (\\u053c\\u0565\\u057c\\u0576\\u0561\\u0575\\u056b\\u0576 \\u0542\\u0561\\u0580\\u0561\\u0562\\u0561\\u0572\\u056b) \\u0540\\u0561\\u0576\\u0580\\u0561\\u057a\\u0565\\u057f\\u0578\\u0582\\u0569\\u0575\\u0561\\u0576 \\u0561\\u0576\\u057e\\u057f\\u0561\\u0576\\u0563\\u0578\\u0582\\u0569\\u0575\\u0561\\u0576 \\u056d\\u0578\\u0580\\u0570\\u0580\\u0564\\u056b \\u057a\\u0561\\u057f\\u0574\\u0578\\u0582\\u0569\\u0575\\u0578\\u0582\\u0576\",\"ru\":\"\\u0418\\u0441\\u0442\\u043e\\u0440\\u0438\\u044f \\u0421\\u043e\\u0432\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430 \\u0411\\u0435\\u0437\\u043e\\u043f\\u0430\\u0441\\u043d\\u043e\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438 \\u0420\\u0435\\u0441\\u043f\\u0443\\u0431\\u043b\\u0438\\u043a\\u0438 \\u0410\\u0440\\u0446\\u0430\\u0445 (\\u041d\\u0430\\u0433\\u043e\\u0440\\u043d\\u043e\\u0433\\u043e \\u041a\\u0430\\u0440\\u0430\\u0431\\u0430\\u0445\\u0430)\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>By the decree of the President of the Republic of Artsakh the Office of the Security Council of the Artsakh Republic was established as a state administrative institution and the charter and structure of the Office was approved on July 4, 2020.<\\/p><p>The Charter of the Security Council of the Republic of Artsakh was approved by the decree of the President of the Republic of Artsakh on July 26, 2020.<\\/p><p>Samvel Andranik Babayan was appointed Secretary of the Security Council of the Republic of Artsakh by the decree of the President of the Republic of Artsakh on May 29, 2020.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the President of the Republic of Artsakh on May 18, 2020, Arshavir Suren Gharamyan was dismissed from the post of the Secretary of the Security Council of the Republic of Artsakh, due to resignation.<\\/p><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f69fff005b56.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f69fffaa436d.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><p>&nbsp;<\\/p><p>By the decree of the President of the Republic of Artsakh on June 26, 2019, Arshavir Gharamyan was appointed Secretary of the Security Council of the Republic of Artsakh, resigning from the post of Special Representative of the President of the Republic of Artsakh.<\\/p><p>On June 11, 2019, by the decree of the President of the Artsakh Republic, Vitaly Mikhael Balasanyan was dismissed from the post of the Secretary of the Security Council of the Artsakh Republic.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President on November 3, 2016, Vitaly Mikhael Balasanyan was appointed Secretary of the NKR Security Council.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President on November 3, 2016, Victor Mikhael Kocharyan was appointed Deputy Secretary of the NKR Security Council, resigning from the post of Secretary of the NKR Security Council.<\\/p><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f6a0006e9258.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f6a000b94dde.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><p>&nbsp;<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President of October 29, 2014, Victor Mikhael Kocharyan was appointed Secretary of the NKR Security Council, resigning from the post of Director of the National Security Service under the NKR Government.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President on October 29, 2014, the Chief of Staff of the NKR President, Secretary of the Security Council Marat Shmavon Musayelyan was appointed Chief of Staff of the NKR President, resigning from the post of the Secretary of the NKR Security Council.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President on May 7, 2008, the composition of the NKR Security Council was approved. By the same degree, the NKR President\\u2019s decrees on September 8, 1998 and on April 12, 2004 were declared invalid.<\\/p><p>By the decree of the NKR President on May 7, 2008, the Chief of Staff of the NKR President Marat Shmavon Musayelyan was appointed the Secretary of the NKR Security Council.<\\/p><p>By the NKR President\\u2019s decree on May 7, 2008, Karen Zarmayr Baburyan was dismissed from the post of the Secretary of the NKR Security Council.<\\/p><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f6a0022534e2.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><figure class=\\\"image\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/editor\\/5f6a002828980.jpg\\\"><\\/figure><p>The staffs of the NKR President and the NKR Security Council reorganized the staff of the NKR President by the decree of the NKR President on March 23, 2006.<\\/p><p>The charters, the staff and the structure of the staff of the NKR Security Council were approved&nbsp;by the decree of the NKR President on April 12, 2004. The decree on approving the charters of the NKR Security Council, the Secretary of the Security Council and the structure of the Secretary\\u2019s staff were expired on September 8, 1998.<\\/p><p>Karen Zarmaryr Baburyan was appointed the Secretary of the NKR Security Council by the NKR President\\u2019s decree on April 19, 2001.<\\/p><p>Slava Avanes Avanesyan was dismissed from the post of Secretary of the NKR Security Council for another work place by the decree of the NKR President on September 25, 2000.<\\/p><p>The composition of the Security Council was approved by the NKR President\\u2019s decree on September 8, 1998. By the same decree, the NKR President\\u2019s decree on February 7, 1995, on the Security Council under the NKR President expired.<\\/p><p>Slava Avanes Avanesyan was appointed the Secretary of the NKR Security Council by the decree of the NKR President on June 22, 1998.<\\/p><p>The Security Council under the NKR President was established by the decree of the NKR President on February 7, 1995.<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p><p>&nbsp;*The information provided is incomplete, taking into account the confidentiality of existing functions of the Security Council.<\\/p>\",\"hy\":\"<p>2020&nbsp;\\u0569\\u057e\\u0561\\u056f\\u0561\\u0576\\u056b \\u0570\\u0578\\u0582\\u056c\\u05