obank\\\" Askeran branch manager.<\\/p><p><strong>1999-2004<\\/strong> \\\"Armagrobank\\\" Stepanakert branch manager.<\\/p><p><strong>2005<\\/strong> -Deputy of the NKR National Assembly. Head of \\\"Hayreniq\\\" (Homeland) faction, chairman of the Standing Committee on Budget, Financial and Economic Management.<\\/p><p><strong>2005-2007<\\/strong> and <strong>from 2009 to the present day <\\/strong>- Chairman of the \\\"Azat Hayreniq\\\" (Free Homeland) party.<\\/p><p><strong>2006-2007 <\\/strong>- CEO, Karabakh Gold CJSC.<\\/p><p><strong>On 14 September 2007<\\/strong>, by the decree of President of the Nagorno Karabakh Republic, Arayik Haroutyunyan was appointed Premier of the Nagorno Karabakh Republic.<\\/p><p><strong>On 14 September 2012<\\/strong>, by the decree of President of the Nagorno Karabakh Republic, Arayik Haroutyunyan was reappointed Premier of the Nagorno Karabakh Republic.<\\/p><p><strong>On 25 September 2017<\\/strong>, by the decree of President of the Artsakh Karabakh Republic, Arayik Haroutyunyan was appointed Artsakh Republic State Minister.<\\/p><p><strong>June 6, 2018 <\\/strong>- was released from the post of State Minister upon his own request.<\\/p><p><strong>July 2, 2018<\\/strong> - by the decree of the Artsakh Republic President was appointed advisor to the Artsakh Republic President - Artsakh Republic President\'s representative at large.<\\/p><p><strong>21 February, 2019 <\\/strong>- by the decree of the Artsakh Republic President was released from the post of advisor to the Artsakh Republic President - Artsakh Republic President\'s representative at large upon his own request.<\\/p><p><strong>In February 2020 <\\/strong>was nominated for the post of Artsakh Republic President by \\u00abAzat Hayreniq - UCA\\u00bb parties coalition and passed to the second tour at the result of state elections held at 31st March.<\\/p><p>At the second tour held on <strong>April 14th<\\/strong> became Artsakh Republic President with votes of 88 percen