he Republic of Armenia, document that reflects the security challenges and threats of the pan-Armenians, the principles and ways to overcome them, was approved.<\\/p><p>This key component of the security policy of the Republic of Armenia refers to Artsakh, a key component of the pan-Armenian agenda, with a separate sub-chapter \\\"Ensuring the Security of Artsakh\\\", which is not accidentally combined with the independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of Armenia.The global-regional transformations, which are reflected in the national security strategy of the Republic of Armenia, nevertheless have not changed Armenia\'s view on the Azerbaijani-Karabakh conflict as the main challenge of the Republic of Armenia, the use of force by Azerbaijan as the main threat of the Republic of ArmeniaIn this context, the Artsakh Republic will continue the cooperation with the Republic of Armenia, with the following features:<\\/p><ol><li>Adhering to the mediation mission of the OSCE Minsk Group, we continue to stand for a peaceful settlement of the Azerbaijani-Karabakh conflict on a compromise basis.<\\/li><li>The principle of the right of nations to self-determination enshrined in the United Nations declarations and international human rights treaties will be the basis for the peaceful settlement of the Azerbaijani-Karabakh conflict as the exclusive right of the Artsakh Armenians to decide their own destiny.<\\/li><li>Artsakh will be transformed from an object of conflict into a subject, thus directly realizing the subjectivity of the authorities elected by the people of Artsakh.<\\/li><li>There is no alternative to the international recognition of the Artsakh Republic<\\/li><li>The security of Artsakh is not subject to bargaining under any circumstances.&nbsp;Based on the above-mentioned historical, political and legal grounds, the Office of the Security Council of the Artsakh Republic is developing conceptual approaches to the settlement of the Azerbaijani-Karabakh conflict, which will be put up for public discussion with the involvement of interested parts.<\\/li><\\/ol><p>&nbsp;<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}', '2020-09-10 00:00:00', '2020-09-17 00:00:00'),
